I never woulda guessed that your street clothes

268
00:12:44,525 --> 00:12:45,567
would be so boy-ish.

269
00:12:45,650 --> 00:12:46,817
I'm surprised.

270
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:48,609
It looks pretty cute on you.

271
00:12:50,692 --> 00:12:53,025
Um, well, no, actually, this is just my, uh...

272
00:12:53,109 --> 00:12:56,025
I'm so used to you being all
serious with that lab coat on,

273
00:12:56,109 --> 00:12:59,067
so seeing you like this makes you seem cuter, I guess.

274
00:13:01,775 --> 00:13:03,525
I'll have to retreat for today!

275
00:13:03,609 --> 00:13:05,775
Hang on, you forgot your science thingy!

276
00:13:09,442 --> 00:13:10,859
So then,

277
00:13:10,942 --> 00:13:12,525
have you given any thought to what you might

278
00:13:12,609 --> 00:13:15,359
want to do in the future at all, Miss Minakami?

279
00:13:15,442 --> 00:13:16,859
I have thought about it.

280
00:13:19,442 --> 00:13:23,067
Uh... So, are you planning on finding a job?

281
00:13:23,150 --> 00:13:27,900
Then... are you... looking into higher education?

282
00:13:27,984 --> 00:13:33,650
Uh... 'Kay that means...

283
00:13:35,275 --> 00:13:38,442
I think I get it.

284
00:13:52,734 --> 00:13:54,609
Hey, you find it yet?

285
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:56,817
It's no good.

286
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:58,400
We can't find the cube.

287
00:13:58,484 --> 00:13:59,650
I thought we stored that thing

288
00:13:59,734 --> 00:14:00,567
somewhere safe.

289
00:14:00,650 --> 00:14:02,734
How could it just disappear?

290
00:14:02,817 --> 00:14:04,150
Well, look on the bright side.

291
00:14:04,234 --> 00:14:05,734
There's gonna be a huge cash reward

292
00:14:05,817 --> 00:14:07,442
for whoever finds the dang thing.

293
00:14:07,525 --> 00:14:08,859
I'd say that's worth all the trouble

294
00:14:08,942 --> 00:14:09,984
we're going through.

295
00:14:10,067 --> 00:14:11,317
Ha, yeah!

296
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:13,317
If we can find one, then we can find the other.

297
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:14,775
Better keep looking.

298
00:14:14,859 --> 00:14:17,150
If I could just get my hands on that cube.

299
00:14:17,234 --> 00:14:19,359
I wonder if that would help me
get in the King's good graces.

300
00:14:19,442 --> 00:14:21,359
Hey, uh, who's that?

301
00:14:21,442 --> 00:14:22,234
Over there?

302
00:14:22,317 --> 00:14:23,650
Huh?

303
00:14:28,442 --> 00:14:29,859
My wooden cube.

304
00:14:29,942 --> 00:14:31,692
Give it back.

305
00:14:36,484 --> 00:14:37,734
Hey, now.

306
00:14:37,817 --> 00:14:40,275
What seems to be the big problem here, little girl?

307
00:14:40,359 --> 00:14:42,150
How did you manage to get on this ship?

308
00:14:42,234 --> 00:14:43,025
Don't tell me.

309
00:14:43,109 --> 00:14:45,317
You're some kind of stowaway?

310
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:47,942
Do you know how we punish kids for doing that?

311
00:14:48,025 --> 00:14:49,859
We throw them straight into prison.

312
00:14:49,942 --> 00:14:51,192
Ten years minimum.

313
00:14:51,275 --> 00:14:53,692
And the worst part is, I'd be your warden!

314
00:14:53,775 --> 00:14:54,692
That what you want?

315
00:14:56,317 --> 00:14:57,275
No, 22!

316
00:14:57,359 --> 00:14:58,900
Damn it! You're gonna pay!

317
00:14:58,984 --> 00:15:00,900
Hold it. I can handle this.

318
00:15:00,984 --> 00:15:03,484
I got careless for a split second there.

319
00:15:03,567 --> 00:15:06,150
But I've got this under control now, trust me.

320
00:15:06,234 --> 00:15:07,525
I gotta say.

321
00:15:07,609 --> 00:15:10,025
You sure do pack quite a powerful punch

322
00:15:10,109 --> 00:15:11,734
for such a tiny girl.

323
00:15:11,817 --> 00:15:12,734
Now then.

324
00:15:12,817 --> 00:15:14,234
This has been fun,

325
00:15:14,317 --> 00:15:16,817
but it's time you started talk--

326
00:15:18,525 --> 00:15:19,442
Is he okay?

327
00:15:19,525 --> 00:15:20,650
Negative. He's dead.

328
00:15:20,734 --> 00:15:21,519
She's a monster!

329
00:15:21,544 --> 00:15:24,275
The stowaway isn't gonna stop
until she gets the wooden cube!

330
00:15:24,359 --> 00:15:25,692
Let's charge at her together!

331
00:15:25,775 --> 00:15:27,400
We've got her outnumbered.

332
00:15:27,484 --> 00:15:28,734
Hmm.

333
00:15:28,817 --> 00:15:30,067
There's no reason to panic,

334
00:15:30,150 --> 00:15:32,484
now that I'm here, so everybody can settle down.

335
00:15:32,567 --> 00:15:33,984
Officer!

336
00:15:37,859 --> 00:15:40,984
Relax. Just sit back and watch how it's done.

337
00:15:41,067 --> 00:15:42,484
In this situation,

338
00:15:42,567 --> 00:15:45,275
the Officer might actually be our only hope.

339
00:15:45,359 --> 00:15:47,442
Hmm. So, she's on a solo mission

340
00:15:47,525 --> 00:15:49,025
to claim the wooden cube.

341
00:15:49,109 --> 00:15:53,109
Undoubtedly a highly-skilled
agent sent by an unknown enemy.

342
00:15:53,192 --> 00:15:55,984
All that skill and power could be quite useful, though,

343
00:15:56,067 --> 00:15:59,192
if we can convince her to switch over to our side.

344
00:15:59,275 --> 00:16:02,484
Fortunately, I am in possession of the other wooden cube.

345
00:16:02,567 --> 00:16:03,775
It's what she wants,

346
00:16:03,859 --> 00:16:05,775
so it makes the perfect bargaining chip,

347
00:16:05,859 --> 00:16:08,609
and we should be able to come to an agreement.

348
00:16:08,692 --> 00:16:11,192
I just happen to have the cube you're looking for,

349
00:16:11,275 --> 00:16:13,317
so what do you say we make a trade?

350
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:15,275
We could strike a promising deal--

351
00:16:15,359 --> 00:16:16,984
Ooh!

352
00:16:26,025 --> 00:16:26,942
Officer!

353
00:16:27,025 --> 00:16:28,192
He's dead, too!

354
00:16:28,275 --> 00:16:29,734
This is not good!

355
00:16:29,817 --> 00:16:31,900
She took down the Officer like it was nothing!

356
00:16:31,984 --> 00:16:33,067
We'll show you!

357
00:16:33,150 --> 00:16:35,609
We're not gonna let you out of here alive!

358
00:16:35,692 --> 00:16:38,317
This is bad! Really, really bad!

359
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:41,859
By definition, that means it's not good.

360
00:16:43,609 --> 00:16:44,984
What does that mean, Scholar?

361
00:16:45,067 --> 00:16:46,609
How bad is "really, really bad"?

362
00:16:46,692 --> 00:16:49,025
If you would all stop yelling at me for a moment

363
00:16:49,109 --> 00:16:50,442
and observe the intruder's head,

364
00:16:50,525 --> 00:16:52,734
you'll notice that she has a wooden cube in her hair.

365
00:16:52,817 --> 00:16:54,400
And if you look on the other side of her head,

366
00:16:54,484 --> 00:16:56,609
there's another wooden cube.

367
00:16:56,692 --> 00:16:58,942
Meaning that she has a total of two wooden cubes!

368
00:16:59,025 --> 00:17:01,567
Which means that she has both
wooden cubes in her possession!

369
00:17:01,650 --> 00:17:03,067
But even if she has

370
00:17:03,150 --> 00:17:04,275
both the cubes,

371
00:17:04,359 --> 00:17:05,400
we should be fine as long as she doesn't know

372
00:17:05,484 --> 00:17:06,859
how to summon the ancient weapon.

373
00:17:06,942 --> 00:17:08,317
That's right! We can still win if--

374
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:10,109
Shut up and listen to me!

375
00:17:10,192 --> 00:17:11,775
It says here in the Hell Encyclopedia,

376
00:17:11,859 --> 00:17:13,734
that whoever possesses both of the wooden cubes

377
00:17:13,817 --> 00:17:15,525
will be bestowed with the unstoppable power

378
00:17:15,609 --> 00:17:17,525
of the ancient weapon!

379
00:17:17,609 --> 00:17:18,942
In other words,

380
00:17:19,025 --> 00:17:21,442
it means that whoever possesses both of the wooden cubes

381
00:17:21,525 --> 00:17:23,275
will be bestowed with the unstoppable power

382
00:17:23,359 --> 00:17:24,567
of the ancient weapon.

383
00:17:24,650 --> 00:17:25,442
What does that mean?

384
00:17:25,525 --> 00:17:26,817
Explain that once more, please!

385
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:28,609
Yeah, I didn't get it the first time!

386
00:17:28,692 --> 00:17:29,650
In other--

387
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:32,859
There's no time to explain!

388
00:17:32,942 --> 00:17:34,234
It is over!

389
00:17:34,317 --> 00:17:36,067
If we try to fight here, not only will we be doomed,

390
00:17:36,150 --> 00:17:38,234
but the entire world along with us!

391
00:17:45,067 --> 00:17:46,234
Don't you dare back down!

392
00:17:48,109 --> 00:17:49,859
Never run from you fears!

393
00:17:49,942 --> 00:17:51,359
Conquer them!

394
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:54,484
It's the Captain!

395
00:17:54,567 --> 00:17:56,025
Captain!

396
00:17:56,109 --> 00:17:57,150
All right!

397
00:17:57,234 --> 00:17:58,734
Listen. Trying to attack her

398
00:17:58,817 --> 00:18:01,984
head-on one at a time will only guarantee your demise.

399
00:18:02,067 --> 00:18:03,567
It would be futile.

400
00:18:03,650 --> 00:18:06,150
However! The enemy is but one lone girl!

401
00:18:06,234 --> 00:18:08,442
So we have the advantage of numbers on our side!

402
00:18:08,525 --> 00:18:10,317
We must work together as a complete unit

403
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:12,109
to rush in and take those wooden cubes from her

404
00:18:12,192 --> 00:18:13,484
no matter the cost!

405
00:18:13,567 --> 00:18:15,525
I'll take point and lead the vanguard!

406
00:18:15,609 --> 00:18:17,817
Attack!

407
00:18:20,567 --> 00:18:22,234
Captain!

408
00:18:22,317 --> 00:18:24,234
Forget about me! Carry on!

409
00:18:24,317 --> 00:18:25,525
But, we can't just--

410
00:18:25,609 --> 00:18:26,859
You piddling maggot!

411
00:18:26,942 --> 00:18:28,317
I don't remember training a pathetic,

412
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:30,234
cowardly soldier like you!

413
00:18:39,150 --> 00:18:40,567
It's all over.

414
00:18:40,650 --> 00:18:42,150
The Officer is gone.

415
00:18:42,234 --> 00:18:44,442
The Captain is stuck in a hole.

416
00:18:44,525 --> 00:18:46,192
What hope do we have left now?

417
00:18:46,275 --> 00:18:47,234
We're a team.

418
00:18:47,317 --> 00:18:49,317
And we still have each other.

419
00:18:51,275 --> 00:18:54,984
One for all... and all for one!

420
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:17,442
Captain, no!

421
00:19:17,525 --> 00:19:21,984
It's been 12 long years since I joined this squad.

422
00:19:23,317 --> 00:19:27,525
Over a decade of my life gone in a flash,

423
00:19:27,609 --> 00:19:30,692
because of this girl.

424
00:19:32,359 --> 00:19:34,150
It can't be over.

425
00:19:35,317 --> 00:19:37,817
I'm not done yet.

426
00:19:37,900 --> 00:19:44,359
It won't end like this!

427
00:20:03,067 --> 00:20:04,317
We're doomed!

428
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:05,234
Please, no!

429
00:20:05,317 --> 00:20:07,025
I don't wanna die here!

430
00:20:31,234 --> 00:20:32,609
Huh?

431
00:20:34,567 --> 00:20:36,400
I'll go stand in the hallway.

432
00:20:44,359 --> 00:20:45,150
Huh?

433
00:20:45,234 --> 00:20:46,942
That's so obvious!

434
00:20:47,025 --> 00:20:48,192
Whatever.

435
00:20:48,275 --> 00:20:49,859
I've got nothing else to do right now,

436
00:20:49,942 --> 00:20:52,025
so I might as well indulge the little brat.

437
00:20:54,817 --> 00:20:57,150
Making something a waste of time

438
00:20:57,234 --> 00:20:59,650
is a special talent indeed.

439
00:21:07,442 --> 00:21:08,525
Hmm.

440
00:21:10,150 --> 00:21:11,359
Oh, you have bed-head.

441
00:21:11,442 --> 00:21:13,817
It's actually pretty cute on you.

442
00:21:14,942 --> 00:21:16,859
It looks pretty cute on you.

443
00:21:29,192 --> 00:21:30,650
What the hell am I doing?

444
00:21:30,734 --> 00:21:32,650
What's wrong with me?

445
00:21:36,359 --> 00:21:37,525
I'm finished now!

446
00:21:37,609 --> 00:21:39,900
The bath is all yours whenever you--

447
00:23:26,859 --> 00:23:28,109
I'm a Love Umbrella.

448
00:23:28,192 --> 00:23:30,359
If you need a matchmaker, I've got you covered!

449
00:23:30,442 --> 00:23:31,609
Write your name on one side,

450
00:23:31,692 --> 00:23:33,567
and your special someone on the other.

451
00:23:33,650 --> 00:23:34,942
Oh? You don't have one?

452
00:23:35,025 --> 00:23:36,525
Then for a sad sap like you,

453
00:23:36,609 --> 00:23:39,150
the next <i>My Ordinary Life</i> is Episode 22.

454
00:23:39,234 --> 00:23:40,775
Look forward to it!

